parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to shudder or hesitate during acceleration, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially in stop-and-go traffic, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shudders or hesitates during acceleration
especially between 20-40 mph
the vehicle hesitates for a brief period before accelerating
the drivetrain/transmission shudders
the vehicle runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission solenoid can cause the engine to stall, the vehicle to run rough, and multiple warning lights to illuminate, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalls
vehicle runs rough
check engine light
ATOIL light
VSC light
and cruise control light illuminate
transmission solenoid problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Lockup or Excessive Travel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal lockup or excessive travel can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes rock hard and cannot be pressed
the brake pedal seizes up after initial press
the brake pedal has excessive travel
the brake pedal locks into place
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

the fuel gauge drops suddenly.
